Bugs caught + fixed during validation:
- run-multinode-rsync-host{1,2}.sh and run-multinode-nfsordma-host1.sh: `sudo chmod -R 777`
  alone insufficient for root-owned ckpt dirs; subsequent rsync as $USER failed mtime
  updates → exit 23 → script abort. Fix: add `sudo chown -R "$USER:$USER" ${RUN_DIR}/checkpoints`
  after each training run, before the chmod.

Kit reproduces all artifact-grade qualitative findings within ±15% drift on this
controlled run.
